<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06196241 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06196241 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Police on Saturday were investigating the death of a 23-year-old man who wasgunned down as he sat in a Berkeley barbershop. Officers were called to Stog'sArtistic Barber Shop on Alcatraz Avenue at 7:29 p.m. Friday and found Kevin D.Crowe of Albany inside suffering from gunshot wounds. Crowe was taken toHighland Hospital in Oakland, where he died about four hours later.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Local  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  POLICE INVESTIGATE BARBERSHOP SLAYING  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Bay Area in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910714  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Sunday  </DAY><MONTH>  July  </MONTH><PG.COL>  7B  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  70  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Sunday July 14, 199100196241,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>